</tbody></table></div>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4">Weighted the way a real agent request is composed — mostly English system prompt, tool schemas, code, and JSON — the <strong>new tokenizer comes out around +32% per request</strong>. Chinese barely moved, so the inflation is concentrated on English and code.</p>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4">The whole verification across both tokenizers cost about $0.08 in real API calls.</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">The cross-vendor tokenization gap</h2>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4">The most cited result from the Playcode measurements is the cross-vendor table, with <strong>GPT-5.x's <code>o200k</code> as the 1.00x reference</strong> (it has been frozen and publicly documented for over two years, while Claude's tokenizer is the one that changed):</p>

